<subSubSection id="13791827F807A134E8281124ACC8136F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="41392A52C1CDBEB981F6DC4318F9AEFD" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="07A7B5904844203858DC170721A48618" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Sexual morph: not observed. Asexual morph: Pycnidial stromata ostiolated, immersed in bark, scattered, erumpent through the surface of bark, with multiple locules. Conceptacle black. Ectostromatic disc black, circular to ovoid, (150-)250-300(-375) 
<normalizedToken id="247DEBF22673F946A5D295D72334AF9C" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
diam., with one ostiole per disc. Ostioles black, at the same level as the disc, (40-)50-85(-115) 
<normalizedToken id="251A8CCD629B6FD8962C2EEDD4883614" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
diam. Locule numerous, arranged circularly or elliptically with independent walls, (550-)700-1200(-1350) 
<normalizedToken id="5C0C9F76EBE97FB8E5D7C836DE656A96" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
diam. Peridium comprising few layers of cells of textura angularis, with innermost layer brown, outer layer brown to dark brown. Conidiophores hyaline, unbranched, thin walled, filamentous. Conidiogenous cells enteroblastic polyphialidic, (7.5-)9.5-21(-22.5) 
<normalizedToken id="B2BE192ECEDAA62C5DD3BC12404073C9" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-1.5 
<normalizedToken id="C1F40AEE2B04156F7FD99C375C41A982" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
(x̄ = 15.2 
<normalizedToken id="324BE4192C9F4E83093FD84B28313D06" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.3 
<normalizedToken id="E21FDA1581D63A5FEC61670E7776BB38" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
). Conidia hyaline, allantoid, smooth, aseptate, thin-walled, (3.5-)4.5-5.5(-7) 
<normalizedToken id="8B8045777972557D2554725292BAC495" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-1.5 
<normalizedToken id="7B537E8A58A7FC4FC919133F764A45E4" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
(x̄ = 4.9 
<normalizedToken id="48CA64579E258A38B09FA1967C47140F" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.3 
<normalizedToken id="62C24286D8ADC7F02B4FF5F2EC2A0C86" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="87E661E8CFE87297194FB1CE538A77F5" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="823A48CF6CB8DDF5AE06372A45513991" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Specimens examined.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="552589B1E68CF50ED28FC841E6DB5B4F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
China, Hebei Province, Chengde City, Kuancheng County, chestnut plantation, 
<geoCoordinate id="CC291A4786CBD33C619D7221DAAA3F95" degrees="40" direction="north" minutes="38" orientation="latitude" precision="15" seconds="37" value="40.643612">40°38'37&quot;N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="D25B2D2080EDECBB9DBE4D1FAE3BF1EE" degrees="118" direction="east" minutes="27" orientation="longitude" precision="15" seconds="5" value="118.451385">118°27'5&quot;E</geoCoordinate>
, on branches of 
<taxonomicName id="EEF004883E77CFF450B00C13F850674A" class="Thecofilosea" family="Castanellidae" genus="Castanea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="Castanea mollissima" order="Phaeocalpida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Cercozoa" rank="species" species="mollissima">
<emphasis id="FB730958F14544ECFD2145A75CA443E2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Castanea mollissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 13 October 2017, N. Jiang (BJFC-S1697, living culture CFCC 52461; BJFC-S1698, living culture CFCC 52462).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1C2FD78A076B82CD391D741129619C85" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="95D689941BDBCB62C41B89365158E6DE" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ACC01446C49D044FFD0ADF5697118C96" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="7C6DD284341BBA5FB53521CC55551618" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Valsaceae" genus="Cytospora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Cytospora leucostoma" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="leucostoma">
<emphasis id="09819F9BC9577C26389E0C22C93BA7DF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Cytospora leucostoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a common species causing canker disease on 
<taxonomicName id="E3DA6BDBD384D49338ED08C7F7F8CD2A" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Rosaceae" genus="Cytospora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="family">Rosaceae</taxonomicName>
in China (
<bibRefCitation id="9698681B13B9297386E511482F795A47" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1136/bmj.1.5333.808" author="Teng, SC" journalOrPublisher="Australasian Plant Pathology" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B43" refString="Teng, SC, 1963. Fungi of China. Science Press, 1-808. https://doi.org/10.1136/bmj.1.5333.808" title="Fungi of China. Science Press, 1 - 808." url="https://doi.org/10.1136/bmj.1.5333.808" year="1963">Teng 1963</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="532C53CB41C94E08E5D875C55288B48D" author="Tai, FL" journalOrPublisher="Australasian Plant Pathology" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B42" refString="Tai, FL, 1979. Sylloge fungorum sinicorum. Science Press, 1-1527." title="Sylloge fungorum sinicorum. Science Press, 1 - 1527." year="1979">Tai 1979</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="6184201615A3AE3B476C8A719262354F" author="Wei, JC" journalOrPublisher="Fungal Biology" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B48" refString="Wei, JC, 1979. Identification of Fungus Handbook. Science Press, 1-780." title="Identification of Fungus Handbook. Science Press, 1 - 780." year="1979">Wei 1979</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="302F044EA41C53A4DEC1D20C09567CDF" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3767/persoonia.2020.45.01" author="Fan, XL" journalOrPublisher="Persoonia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 45" refId="B8" refString="Fan, XL, Bezerra, JDP, Tian, CM, Crous, PW, 2020. Cytospora (Diaporthales) in China. Persoonia 45: 1 - 45, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3767/persoonia.2020.45.01" title="Cytospora (Diaporthales) in China." url="https://doi.org/10.3767/persoonia.2020.45.01" volume="45" year="2020">Fan et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
). In this study, fresh specimens were collected from diseased branches of the Chinese chestnut for the first time and identified as 
<taxonomicName id="1EE190C92A0BBBD856DEE24C03B9715A" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Valsaceae" genus="Cytospora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Cytospora leucostoma" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="leucostoma">
<emphasis id="7CEC5A935E21255E1AED5E97C3BF1CEB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Cytospora leucostoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, based on strictly matched asexual morph (4-5.5 
<normalizedToken id="B6C73BAC6FCC198A36E5443DE546C315" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-2 
<normalizedToken id="ABBDB6EA3D83F773D4D9E0DB5E3D5527" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
from 
<taxonomicName id="9ECF248362156E1BA053C74BA57E02AC" class="Thecofilosea" family="Castanellidae" genus="Castanea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="Castanea mollissima" order="Phaeocalpida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Cercozoa" rank="species" species="mollissima">
<emphasis id="D663820E5DAD1019A54E79D6DC4A5B1C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Castanea mollissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in this study vs. 4.5-5.5 
<normalizedToken id="286F90E71FF6812A379C58357F9A31BE" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-1.5 
<normalizedToken id="648EF99ABA6C6387AC60BDB573FE84BE" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
from multiple specimens in 
<bibRefCitation id="5347E664709F47384B878EE93C643DA1" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3767/persoonia.2020.45.01" author="Fan, XL" journalOrPublisher="Persoonia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 45" refId="B8" refString="Fan, XL, Bezerra, JDP, Tian, CM, Crous, PW, 2020. Cytospora (Diaporthales) in China. Persoonia 45: 1 - 45, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3767/persoonia.2020.45.01" title="Cytospora (Diaporthales) in China." url="https://doi.org/10.3767/persoonia.2020.45.01" volume="45" year="2020">Fan et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
) and phylogenic analysis (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="56B5A1C2FC03F3F9A83E53709AD1728C" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Maximum parsimony phylogram of Cytospora obtained from the combined matrix of ITS, LSU, ACT and RPB 2 genes. Bootstrap value ≥ 50 % for MP and ML analyses are presented at the first and second position. Scale bar = 200 nucleotide substitutions. The strains in the current study are in blue and ex-strains are marked with *." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.62.47425.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/371653" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
